Let the two consecutive page numbers be $n$ and $n + 1.$ Then we have the equation $$n(n + 1) = 18{,}360.$$We can write $18{,}360 = 2^3 \cdot 3^2 \cdot 5 \cdot 17 \cdot 19.$ To make the left-hand side into this factorization, we look for factors of $n$ that are one less than $n + 1$ (since then, when we multiply, we will get one factor of $n,$ and one factor of $n + 1$). Checking potential factors starting with $n = 2,$ we find that $n = 170.$

Therefore, the two consecutive page numbers are $170$ and $170 + 1 = 171.$ Their sum is $170 + 171 = \boxed{341}.$

Indeed, notice that $341 = 11^3.$
